  "texts": [
    "For example, in a layer with S = 2048, H = 4096, B = 1, n = 1000, and r = 32 in LLaMA3.1-8B, reduces the activation memory footprint by 50.01% compared to LoRA, which underscore MaCP's efficiency, particularly in memory-constrained environments.",
    "The proposed MaCP is compared with the following baselines: Full Fine-Tuning (FF) updates all parameters of the model.",
    "Adapter Tuning (Houlsby et al., 2019; Lin et al., 2020; Rücklé et al., 2020; Pfeiffer et al., 2020) introduces adapter layers between the self-attention and MLP modules.",
    "LoRA (Hu et al., 2022) approximates weight updates using low-rank matrices to minimize trainable parameters, while AdaLoRA (Zhang et al., 2023) dynamically allocates the parameter budget based on importance scores.",
    "DoRA (Liu et al., 2024) decomposes pre-trained weights into magnitude and direction, applying LoRA for directional updates."
  ],
